# 🇭🇷 ShuddhiCheck AI – Phase II: Croatia Readiness

This folder contains the official readiness brief and rollout strategy for ShuddhiCheck AI’s Phase II expansion into Croatia.

📄 [Download Croatia Readiness Brief (PDF)](./ShuddhiCheckAI_PhaseII_Croatia_Readiness.pdf)

---

## 📌 Key Highlights

- GDPR compliance under AZOP (Croatian Personal Data Protection Agency)
- Ministry of Health leads eHealth and AI modernization efforts
- Strong support from EU-backed innovation hubs
- Bilingual rollout: Croatian required, English supported in pilots

---

## 🏛️ Governance & Innovation Partners

- Ministry of Health – Croatia
- AZOP – Croatian Personal Data Protection Agency
- HZJZ – Croatian Institute of Public Health
- Digital Innovation Hubs Croatia (DIH)
- Ruđer Bošković Institute

---

## 🌐 Language & Localization

| Language     | Role |
|--------------|------|
| **Croatian** | ✅ Required for dashboards, compliance tools, and hospital outreach |
| **English**  | ✅ Accepted for pilots, demos, and scientific collaboration |
| **Minority Languages** | 🟡 Optional in localized contexts (not required nationally) |

🟢 English demo kits and Croatian-language dashboards supported for pilot deployments.

---

## 🛠️ Next Steps

- Upload PDF readiness brief
- Begin outreach to AZOP, HZJZ, and DIH Croatia
- Prepare risk alert tools and localization for Croatian health systems
